what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
We are working with one of the major tertiary hospitals in the UAE to recruit a Consultant Dermatologist. The hospital is accredited by the Joint Commission International (JCI) and offers highly specialised medical care of North American standards catering to local and expatriate populations in Abu Dhabi. The position is well remunerated with a competitive salary and benefits package and provides a good career opportunity to work with one of the USA's top health care providers.
Key Performance Criteria:
Develop an excellent clinical dermatology service in accordance with JCI protocols. Educate and supervise junior medical staff and students Use effectively EHR
Key Qualifications and Experience:
MD or MBBS degree Completion of postgraduate training in North America, UK, Ireland, Australia, South Africa or New Zealand or Western Europe. Hold the appropriate Board Certification or Fellowship for the HAAD Consultant License with Tier 1 qualification.(see below and attached document). The American Board Certification in Dermatology is the preferred qualification for this position but other qualifications suitable for HAAD licensure in the Tier 1 Category will be considered. Minimum of 2 years experience after obtaining Board Certification or Specialist Registration and this should preferably be in a hospital affiliated with a University or with JCI accreditation. Excellent English spoken and written. Arabic language desirable Proficient with IT Familiar with JCI policies and procedures
To apply please send a detailed CV with full employment history and a description of scope of practice.
